OL,3,C'I'll stay until the war is over' -
OL,4,Caid worker living in his car in Ukraine
OL,6,FHe said: "You do see the devastation,
OL,7,Fthe destroyed houses. It's very
OL,8,Fdifferent to see a picture of a
OL,9,Fdestroyed house and then meet the
OL,10,Fperson whose house it was. Then you
OL,11,Fthink, well they've lost their home,
OL,12,Fthey've got no insurance, they're
OL,13,Fmaybe 60 or 70, there's no social
OL,14,Fwelfare. Then you also find out
OL,15,Fthey've lost their son. They've lost
OL,16,Ftheir husband.
OL,18,F"It's a very different story to see a
OL,19,Fpicture of something and actually be
OL,20,Fthere."
